#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Cīvaravagga → akāla­cīvara­sikkhā­pada (kaṅkhāvitāraṇī)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:0.4"
msgid "Cīvaravagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:0.5"
msgid "3. Tatiyakathinasikkhāpada"
msgstr "3. The third training rule on the robe-making season"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli3.203, pts-cs-bu-np3.1.1, pts-vp-en2.24, ms1V_1921
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno akālacīvaraṃ uppannaṃ hoti."
msgstr "At that time a monk had been given robe-cloth outside the robe season."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.3"
msgid "Tassa taṃ cīvaraṃ kayiramānaṃ nappahoti."
msgstr "While he was making the robe, he realized there was not enough cloth."

# NOTE: The point, according to the commentary, is that he was trying to increase its size.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.4"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu taṃ cīvaraṃ ussāpetvā punappunaṃ vimajjati."
msgstr "Lifting it up, he smoothed it out again and again."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.5"
msgid "Addasā kho bhagavā senāsanacārikaṃ āhiṇḍanto taṃ bhikkhuṃ taṃ cīvaraṃ ussāpetvā punappunaṃ vimajjantaṃ."
msgstr "While walking about the dwellings, the Master saw that monk acting in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.6"
msgid "Disvāna yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "He approached him"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.7"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.8"
msgid "“kissa tvaṃ, bhikkhu, imaṃ cīvaraṃ ussāpetvā punappunaṃ vimajjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“What are you doing, monk?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.9"
msgid "“Idaṃ me, bhante, akālacīvaraṃ uppannaṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, I have received this robe-cloth outside the robe season,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.10"
msgid "Kayiramānaṃ nappahoti."
msgstr "but it’s not enough to make a robe."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.11"
msgid "Tenāhaṃ imaṃ cīvaraṃ ussāpetvā punappunaṃ vimajjāmī”ti."
msgstr "That’s why I lift it up and smooth it out again and again.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.12"
msgid "“Atthi pana te, bhikkhu, cīvarapaccāsā”ti?"
msgstr "“Are you expecting to receive more cloth?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.13"
msgid "“Atthi, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“I am.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.14"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā, bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.1.15"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, akālacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā cīvarapaccāsā nikkhipitun”ti."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to keep out-of-season robe-cloth if you are expecting to receive more.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-cs-bu-np3.1.2, pts-vp-en2.25, ms1V_1922
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū—“bhagavatā anuññātaṃ akālacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā cīvarapaccāsā nikkhipitun”ti akālacīvarāni paṭiggahetvā atirekamāsaṃ nikkhipanti."
msgstr "When they knew that the Master had given this allowance, some monks kept robe-cloth for over a month,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.2"
msgid "Tāni cīvarāni cīvaravaṃse bhaṇḍikābaddhāni tiṭṭhanti."
msgstr "in a bundle on a bamboo robe-rack."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.3"
msgid "Addasā kho āyasmā ānando senāsanacārikaṃ āhiṇḍanto tāni cīvarāni cīvaravaṃse bhaṇḍikābaddhāni tiṭṭhante."
msgstr "While walking about the dwellings, Venerable Ānanda saw that robe-cloth,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.4"
msgid "Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "and he asked the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.5"
msgid "“kassimāni, āvuso, cīvarāni cīvaravaṃse bhaṇḍikābaddhāni tiṭṭhantī”ti?"
msgstr "“Whose robe-cloth is this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.6"
msgid "“Amhākaṃ, āvuso, akālacīvarāni cīvarapaccāsā nikkhittānī”ti."
msgstr "“It’s our out-of-season robe-cloth, which we’re keeping because we’re expecting more.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.7"
msgid "“Kīvaciraṃ panāvuso, imāni cīvarāni nikkhittānī”ti?"
msgstr "“How long have you kept this cloth?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.8"
msgid "“Atirekamāsaṃ, āvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Over a month.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.9"
msgid "Āyasmā ānando ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.10"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū akālacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā atirekamāsaṃ nikkhipissantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can these monks keep out-of-season robe-cloth for over a month?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms1V_1923
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.11"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando te bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, Venerable Ānanda told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.12"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū akālacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā atirekamāsaṃ nikkhipantī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that some monks do this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.13"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.14"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.15"
msgid "kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā akālacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā atirekamāsaṃ nikkhipissanti."
msgstr "How can these foolish men keep out-of-season robe-cloth for over a month?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.16"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.17"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.17a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

# NOTE: _Cīvara_ means both a finished robe and any cloth that can be used to make a robe. Thus I vary my translation depending on the context.
#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. REF: sc4, ms1V_1924, pts-vp-en2.26
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.18"
msgid "“Niṭṭhitacīvarasmiṃ bhikkhunā ubbhatasmiṃ kathine bhikkhuno paneva akālacīvaraṃ uppajjeyya, ākaṅkhamānena bhikkhunā paṭiggahetabbaṃ."
msgstr "‘When his robe is finished and the robe-making season has ended, if out-of-season robe-cloth is given to a monk, he may receive it if he wishes."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.19"
msgid "Paṭiggahetvā khippameva kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he receives it, he should quickly make a robe."

#. VAR: māsaparamaṃ tena → māsa­paraman­tena (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.20"
msgid "No cassa pāripūri, māsaparamaṃ tena bhikkhunā taṃ cīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ ūnassa pāripūriyā satiyā paccāsāya."
msgstr "If there is not enough cloth, but he is expecting more, he should keep it at most one month to make up the lack."

#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:1.2.21"
msgid "Tato ce uttari nikkhipeyya, satiyāpi paccāsāya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "If he keeps it beyond that, even if he expects more cloth, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-pli3.204, pts-cs-bu-np3.2.1, ms1V_1925
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.1"
msgid "Niṭṭhitacīvarasminti"
msgstr "When his robe is finished:"

# NOTE: This refers to robe-cloth received during the robe-making season. For details see [](Mv.7.2-7.12).
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.2"
msgid "bhikkhuno cīvaraṃ kataṃ vā hoti naṭṭhaṃ vā vinaṭṭhaṃ vā daḍḍhaṃ vā cīvarāsā vā upacchinnā."
msgstr "the monk has made a robe, or the robe-cloth has been lost, destroyed, or burnt, or he has abandoned his expectation of receiving further robe-cloth."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms1V_1926
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.3"
msgid "Ubbhatasmiṃ kathineti"
msgstr "The robe-making season has ended:"

# NOTE: For an explanation of this see [](Mv.7.1.7) and [](Mv.7.2-7.12).
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.4"
msgid "aṭṭhannaṃ mātikānaṃ aññatarāya mātikāya ubbhataṃ hoti, saṃghena vā antarā ubbhataṃ hoti."
msgstr "it has ended according to one of the eight headings or the Order has ended it, whichever comes first."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_1927
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.5"
msgid "Akālacīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "Out-of-season robe-cloth:"

# NOTE: That is, in-season robe-cloth is cloth obtained during the last month of the rainy season, while out-of-season robe-cloth is cloth obtained during the remaining eleven months of the year. See [](Kkh. 101.28).
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.6"
msgid "anatthate kathine ekādasamāse uppannaṃ,"
msgstr "if the robe-making ceremony has not been done, robe-cloth that is given during the eleven months."

# NOTE: That is, in-season robe-cloth is cloth obtained during the last month of the rainy season or during the cold season, while out-of-season robe-cloth is cloth obtained during the remaining seven months of the year. See [](Kkh.101.28).
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.7"
msgid "atthate kathine sattamāse uppannaṃ,"
msgstr "If the robe-making ceremony has been done, robe-cloth that is given during the seven months."

# NOTE: According to the commentary “designated” means designated as out-of-season cloth or designated to an individual: _Kālepi ādissa dinnanti saṅghassa vā “idaṃ akālacīvaran”ti uddisitvā dinnaṃ, ekapuggalassa vā “idaṃ tuyhaṃ dammī”ti dinnaṃ,_ “‘Also, if it is given in the robe season, but it is designated’ means: it is given to the Order after designating it by saying, ‘This is out-of-season robe-cloth’, or it is given to an individual by saying, ‘I give this to you’.” The commentary to _bhikkhunī nissaggiya pācittiya_ 2 adds that designating to a group is included in designated cloth: _Ādissa dinnanti sampattā bhājentūti vatvāpi idaṃ gaṇassa idaṃ tumhākaṃ dammīti vatvā vā dātukamyatāya pādamūle ṭhapetvā vā dinnampi ādissa dinnaṃ nāma hoti; etaṃ sabbampi akālacīvaraṃ;_ “‘Given after designating’ means: if they give after saying, ‘Let those who are present share it out,’ or after saying, ‘I give this to the group, to you,’ or they place it at the feet (of the recipient) wishing to give, this is called ‘given after designating’. All this is called out-of-season robe-cloth.”
# NOTE: See [](Kkh.102.1).
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.8"
msgid "kālepi ādissa dinnaṃ, etaṃ akālacīvaraṃ nāma."
msgstr "Also, if it is given in the robe season, but the cloth is designated, it is called “out-of-season robe-cloth.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, pts-vp-en2.27, ms1V_1928
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.9"
msgid "Uppajjeyyāti"
msgstr "Is given:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.10"
msgid "uppajjeyya saṃghato vā gaṇato vā ñātito vā mittato vā paṃsukūlaṃ vā attano vā dhanena."
msgstr "Is given by the Order, by a group, by a relative, or by a friend, or there are rags, or it is by means of his own property."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms1V_1929
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.11"
msgid "Ākaṅkhamānenāti"
msgstr "If he wishes:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.12"
msgid "icchamānena paṭiggahetabbaṃ."
msgstr "if he desires, he may receive it."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_1930
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.13"
msgid "Paṭiggahetvā khippameva kāretabbanti"
msgstr "If he receives it, he should quickly make a robe:"

# NOTE: That is, in accordance with the first rule of this section, [](Relinquishment 1).
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.14"
msgid "dasāhā kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "it should be made within ten days."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_1931
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.15"
msgid "No cassa pāripūrīti"
msgstr "If there is not enough cloth:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.16"
msgid "kayiramānaṃ nappahoti."
msgstr "if there is not enough cloth when the robe is being made."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_1932
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.17"
msgid "Māsaparamaṃ tena bhikkhunā taṃ cīvaraṃ nikkhipitabbanti"
msgstr "He should keep it at most one month:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.18"
msgid "māsaparamatā nikkhipitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he should keep it for one month at the maximum."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_1933
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.19"
msgid "Ūnassa pāripūriyāti"
msgstr "To make up the lack:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.20"
msgid "ūnassa pāripūratthāya."
msgstr "for the purpose of making up the lack."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_1934
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.21"
msgid "Satiyā paccāsāyāti"
msgstr "But he is expecting more:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.1.22"
msgid "paccāsā hoti saṃghato vā gaṇato vā ñātito vā mittato vā paṃsukūlaṃ vā attano vā dhanena."
msgstr "he is expecting more from the Order, from a group, from a relative, or from a friend, or he is expecting to get rags, or he is expecting to get it by means of his own property."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc15, pts-vp-pli3.205, pts-cs-bu-np3.2.2, ms1V_1935
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.1"
msgid "Tato ce uttari nikkhipeyya satiyāpi paccāsāyāti"
msgstr "If he keeps it beyond that, even if he expects more cloth:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.2"
msgid "tadahuppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, dasāhā kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he receives the expected robe-cloth on the same day as when he received the original robe-cloth, it must be made into a robe within ten days."

# NOTE: The Pali idiom is such that this means on the day after he received the original piece of cloth. (Cf. the definition of ten days in Relinquishment 1, where the eleventh dawn means the tenth dawn after one received the cloth.) The way this works, it seems, is that the day on which the cloth was received counts as one.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.3"
msgid "Dvīhuppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, dasāhā kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he receives the expected robe-cloth two days after he received the original robe-cloth, it must be made into a robe within ten days."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.4"
msgid "Tīhuppanne mūlacīvare … pe …"
msgstr "If he receives the expected robe-cloth three days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.5"
msgid "catūhuppanne …"
msgstr "four days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.6"
msgid "pañcāhuppanne …"
msgstr "five days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.7"
msgid "chāhuppanne …"
msgstr "six days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.8"
msgid "sattāhuppanne …"
msgstr "seven days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.9"
msgid "aṭṭhāhuppanne …"
msgstr "eight days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.10"
msgid "navāhuppanne …"
msgstr "nine days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.11"
msgid "dasāhuppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, dasāhā kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "ten days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.12"
msgid "Ekādase uppanne … pe …"
msgstr "eleven days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.13"
msgid "dvādase uppanne …"
msgstr "twelve days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.14"
msgid "terase uppanne …"
msgstr "thirteen days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.15"
msgid "cuddase uppanne …"
msgstr "fourteen days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.16"
msgid "pannarase uppanne …"
msgstr "fifteen days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.17"
msgid "soḷase uppanne …"
msgstr "sixteen days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.18"
msgid "sattarase uppanne …"
msgstr "seventeen days after …"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.28
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.19"
msgid "aṭṭhārase uppanne …"
msgstr "eighteen days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.20"
msgid "ekūnavīse uppanne …"
msgstr "nineteen days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.21"
msgid "vīse uppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, dasāhā kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "twenty days after he received the original robe-cloth, it must be made into a robe within ten days."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.22"
msgid "Ekavīse uppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, navāhā kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he receives the expected robe-cloth twenty-one days after he received the original robe-cloth, it must be made into a robe within nine days."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.23"
msgid "Dvāvīse uppanne … pe …"
msgstr "If he receives the expected robe-cloth twenty-two days after he received the original robe-cloth, it must be made into a robe within eight days. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.24"
msgid "tevīse uppanne …"
msgstr "twenty-three days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.25"
msgid "catuvīse uppanne …"
msgstr "twenty-four days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.26"
msgid "pañcavīse uppanne …"
msgstr "twenty-five days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.27"
msgid "chabbīse uppanne …"
msgstr "twenty-six days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.28"
msgid "sattavīse uppanne …"
msgstr "twenty-seven days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.29"
msgid "aṭṭhavīse uppanne …"
msgstr "twenty-eight days after …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.30"
msgid "ekūnatiṃse uppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, ekāhaṃ kāretabbaṃ …"
msgstr "If he receives the expected robe-cloth twenty-nine days after he received the original robe-cloth, it must be made into a robe within one day."

# NOTE: Again, according to the commentarial way of counting this refers to the twenty-ninth dawn after the original cloth was received. See the previous note.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.31"
msgid "tiṃse uppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, tadaheva adhiṭṭhātabbaṃ vikappetabbaṃ vissajjetabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he receives the expected robe-cloth thirty days after he received the original robe-cloth, it must be determined, transferred, or given away on that very day."

# NOTE: That is, on the thirtieth dawn after he received the original robe-cloth.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.32"
msgid "No ce adhiṭṭheyya vā vikappeyya vā vissajjeyya vā, ekatiṃse aruṇuggamane nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "If he does not determine it, transfer it, or give it away, it becomes subject to relinquishment at dawn on the thirty-first day."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.33"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe-cloth should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.34"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. HTML: <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.35"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in [Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17](pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13), with appropriate substitutions. "

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.36"
msgid "idaṃ me, bhante, akālacīvaraṃ māsātikkantaṃ nissaggiyaṃ,"
msgstr "‘Venerables, this out-of-season robe-cloth which I have kept for more than a month is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.37"
msgid "imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmīti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.38"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.39"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.40"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe-cloth back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc16, ms1V_1936
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.2.41"
msgid "Visabhāge uppanne mūlacīvare paccāsācīvaraṃ uppajjati, rattiyo ca sesā honti, na akāmā kāretabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he obtains the expected robe-cloth, but it is different from the robe-cloth originally obtained, and there are days remaining, he does not have to make a robe if he does not want to."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc17, pts-cs-bu-np3.2.3, ms1V_1937
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.1"
msgid "Māsātikkante atikkantasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than a month and he perceives it as more than a month, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.2"
msgid "Māsātikkante vematiko nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than a month, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.3"
msgid "Māsātikkante anatikkantasaññī nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is more than a month, but he perceives it as less than a month, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.4"
msgid "Anadhiṭṭhite adhiṭṭhitasaññī … pe …"
msgstr "If it has not been determined, but he perceives it as determined, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.5"
msgid "avikappite vikappitasaññī …"
msgstr "If it has not been transferred, but he perceives it as transferred, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.29
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.6"
msgid "avissajjite vissajjitasaññī …"
msgstr "If it has not been given away, but he perceives it as given away, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.7"
msgid "anaṭṭhe naṭṭhasaññī …"
msgstr "If it has not been lost, but he perceives it as lost, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.8"
msgid "avinaṭṭhe vinaṭṭhasaññī …"
msgstr "If it has not been destroyed, but he perceives it as destroyed, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.9"
msgid "adaḍḍhe daḍḍhasaññī …"
msgstr "If it has not been burnt, but he perceives it as burnt, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.10"
msgid "avilutte viluttasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been stolen, but he perceives it as stolen, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc18, ms1V_1938
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.11"
msgid "Nissaggiyaṃ cīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he uses robe-cloth which should be relinquished without first relinquishing it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.12"
msgid "Māsānatikkante atikkantasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than a month, but he perceives it as more than a month, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.13"
msgid "Māsānatikkante vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than a month, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.3.14"
msgid "Māsānatikkante anatikkantasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is less than a month and he perceives it as less than a month, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.4.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc19, pts-cs-bu-np3.2.4, ms1V_1939
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.4.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.4.2"
msgid "antomāse adhiṭṭheti, vikappeti, vissajjeti, nassati, vinassati, ḍayhati, acchinditvā gaṇhanti, vissāsaṃ gaṇhanti,"
msgstr "if within a month it has been determined, transferred, given away, lost, destroyed, burnt, stolen, or taken on trust;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.4.3"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.4.4"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc20, ms1V_1940
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np3:2.4.5"
msgid "Tatiyakathinasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr "The third rule, the third training rule on the robe-making season, is finished."
